(0,0)
P=(X,Y)
 A = (p,0) \\ B= (-\frac{q}2,\frac{\sqrt{3}}2q) \\ C=(-\frac{r}2,-\frac{\sqrt{3}}2r)  
s(X,Y)=PA + PB + PC= \\ \left((X-p)^2 +Y^2\right)^{\frac12}+\left((X+\frac{q}2)^2 +(Y-\frac{\sqrt{3}q}2)^2\right)^{\frac12}+\left((X+\frac{r}2)^2 +(Y+\frac{\sqrt{3}}2r)^2\right)^{\frac12}
\frac{\partial s}{ \partial x}|_{(0,0)} = 0 \\ \frac{\partial s}{ \partial y}|_{(0,0)} = 0 
s(0,0) = p+q+r 
